parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Accelerator Pedal Sticking or Floor Mat Interference
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck to the floorboard
the vehicle accelerates independently without warning
the brake pedal fails to slow the vehicle
the vehicle speeds out of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently without warning
the accelerator pedal sticks or fails to respond
the vehicle fails to start
the instrument panel flickers
and the windshield wipers operate independently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Heater actuator failure can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The heater stops working when turned on
the heater actuator fails prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective felt wheel liners can cause a safety hazard, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The felt wheel liners become torn and dislodged when going through puddles or normal road conditions
especially when it's raining. Once dislodged
they can fly up underneath the vehicle and hit objects
vehicles
or people
or cause adverse events by running against the wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden brake system lockup can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake system locks all wheels while driving
resulting in a sudden stop
loud squeaking sound
and black track marks on the road. No warning lights or service lights appear on the dashboard before or after the incident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tire failure can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The tire blows out suddenly
with the sidewall separating on the street side
even at low mileage (850 miles). The tire handles well before the failure
but the sudden blowout can be unexpected and catastrophic.
